561
00:34:04,720 --> 00:34:08,000
My mom is very emotional though.

562
00:34:09,680 --> 00:34:12,720
She even hits me sometimes.

563
00:34:16,280 --> 00:34:17,480
Don't worry, Xiaomeng.

564
00:34:18,200 --> 00:34:20,280
I believe Aunt will get well soon.

565
00:34:21,680 --> 00:34:22,560
I hope so.

566
00:34:23,440 --> 00:34:24,240
Right.

567
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:25,840
Didn't you had a job interview previously?

568
00:34:26,080 --> 00:34:27,080
Have you heard from them?

569
00:34:28,320 --> 00:34:29,240
I went,

570
00:34:29,640 --> 00:34:31,400
and met with the person in charge.

571
00:34:32,240 --> 00:34:34,640
-However...
-Did they love you so much

572
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:36,600
that they hired you on the spot?

573
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:38,600
Qiao Zhen,

574
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:40,720
I think that production company

575
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:42,040
is not suitable for me.

576
00:34:42,320 --> 00:34:44,040
I will figure out something else.

577
00:34:44,320 --> 00:34:45,200
How come?

578
00:34:46,120 --> 00:34:47,400
I thought it was going quite well.

579
00:34:48,200 --> 00:34:50,600
It's nothing. It's just me.

580
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:52,600
I think that

581
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:55,120
their company has a public frontage
after all.

582
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:56,560
At the moment,

583
00:34:56,880 --> 00:34:58,480
I may bring a negative image
to the company.

584
00:35:01,160 --> 00:35:02,120
It's fine.

585
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:03,920
I can look for other jobs.

586
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:06,320
I have just graduated, so there's no rush.

587
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:07,280
I'll take it slowly.

588
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:12,400
It's just a job. It's not a big deal.

589
00:35:12,720 --> 00:35:14,520
If this one doesn't work for you,
we'll find another.

590
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:16,320
Don't worry.

591
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:18,000
After a while,

592
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:20,160
our channel will hire you back.

593
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:24,840
I don't think it's going to happen.

594
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:30,280
I met Zitong some time ago.

595
00:35:30,520 --> 00:35:31,840
She seems to be doing well

596
00:35:32,040 --> 00:35:33,320
and the channel is giving her
opportunities.

597
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:34,840
I'm really happy for her.

598
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:36,640
She has been working very hard.

599
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:38,240
Xiaomeng,

600
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:40,240
don't be so pessimistic.

601
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:43,440
I know that

602
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:46,120
you need a job desperately.

603
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:52,280
Yes, I want to earn money
and be independent as soon as possible.

604
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:54,800
I am my mother's only hope.

605
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:57,320
What's the urgency about?

606
00:35:58,120 --> 00:35:59,720
Did something happen at home again?

607
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:05,760
Don't stress yourself out.

608
00:36:07,120 --> 00:36:09,360
Leave that to me.

609
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:12,960
Right.

610
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:15,200
My friend

611
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:16,920
gave me this today.

612
00:36:17,120 --> 00:36:18,280
Their children's theater

613
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:19,760
is recruiting actors
for a children's play.

614
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:21,640
The wage and benefits are not bad.

615
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:22,680
You shall give it a try.

616
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:24,440
Children's play?

617
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:26,440
Can I do it?

618
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:28,040
Why not?

619
00:36:28,320 --> 00:36:29,760
You are popular among children.

620
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:31,440
They are going to like you.

621
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,560
But recently,

622
00:36:36,720 --> 00:36:39,440
many parents hold a strong view
against me.

623
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:41,480
They are afraid that I would have
a bad impact on their children.

624
00:36:42,480 --> 00:36:43,360
Xiaomeng,

625
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:46,280
the incident has been dying down
gradually.

626
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:49,240
You can't let it hinder your life forever.

627
00:36:52,480 --> 00:36:53,360
Give it a try.

628
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:55,080
Furthermore,

629
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:56,840
they allow flexible working hours,

630
00:36:57,240 --> 00:36:58,640
so it won't be a problem for you
to take care of your mom.

631
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:02,120
All right, I will give it a try.

632
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:08,480
(Project Introduction, Peter Pan)

633
00:37:09,040 --> 00:37:10,040
Peter Pan.

634
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:16,680
Are you crazy?

635
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:28,320
(Resume)

636
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:54,240
Hurry.

637
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:55,440
Look here.

638
00:37:55,680 --> 00:37:56,720
-It's so pretty.
-Come quickly.

639
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:57,720
It's beautiful!

640
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:00,520
-It looks so nice.
-So pretty.

641
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:02,280
Look at this.

642
00:38:02,920 --> 00:38:03,760
It's beautiful.

643
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:08,240
Peter Pan is here.

644
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:13,040
-I...
-What's the matter?

645
00:38:13,560 --> 00:38:14,520
Say the lines.

646
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:17,280
Haven't we just rehearsed?

647
00:38:18,240 --> 00:38:19,960
All right. Let's take five.

648
00:38:20,080 --> 00:38:22,080
Wendy, memorize the lines.

649
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:23,760
You girls, come over here.

650
00:38:26,040 --> 00:38:26,960
I'm telling you,

651
00:38:27,200 --> 00:38:29,000
you all have to push yourself harder.

652
00:38:29,680 --> 00:38:31,440
It's different from the script. Look.

653
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:32,880
The tone is different.

654
00:38:33,120 --> 00:38:34,000
Yes, look here.

655
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:35,200
It's different indeed.

656
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:37,920
What's the matter?

657
00:38:39,040 --> 00:38:41,080
I saw you on the stage.

658
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:42,320
Did you forget your lines?

659
00:38:43,120 --> 00:38:44,280
I was a bit nervous.

660
00:38:44,600 --> 00:38:46,280
I didn't know what I was thinking.

661
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:48,680
Are you still in school?

662
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:51,760
Peter Pan and I are both freshmen
in the university.

663
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:53,600
We don't have many experiences
in performing art.

664
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:55,760
It's fine.

665
00:38:55,920 --> 00:38:57,520
When you get more familiar with the lines

666
00:38:57,680 --> 00:38:58,640
and the stage,

667
00:38:58,720 --> 00:38:59,680
you will act more natural.

668
00:39:01,080 --> 00:39:03,040
I still remember my first time
being in front of the camera,

669
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:05,320
I also did very poorly.

670
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:06,880
Are you an actor, too?

671
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:08,680
I...

672
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:12,080
I was a host for a children's program.

673
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:13,880
You...

674
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:15,400
You are Miss Xiaomeng.

675
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:19,360
That's me.

676
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:22,040
I have heard about you.

677
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:25,880
Yes,

678
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:28,080
I had some negative news previously.

679
00:39:28,680 --> 00:39:29,480
After that,

680
00:39:30,280 --> 00:39:31,800
I quitted being the host.

681
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:35,080
No, I don't think it was your fault.

682
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:37,120
What you did behind the camera

683
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:38,600
is your private life.

684
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:39,920
You don't have to care about

685
00:39:39,960 --> 00:39:42,200
the moral judgment
and censure of the public.

686
00:39:43,200 --> 00:39:45,520
People who like you
would not care what you do.

687
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:46,880
People who don't like you

688
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,680
would not be happy with anything
that you do.

689
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:52,040
So I think you don't need to care about
what the others think.

690
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:55,720
I didn't expect you to be so...

691
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:57,560
Weird, right?

692
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:00,480
I think you are right.

693
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:01,760
You are so brave.

694
00:40:02,120 --> 00:40:03,160
I believe

695
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:06,000
you could do a much better
performance on stage.

696
00:40:07,040 --> 00:40:08,240
After chatting with you,

697
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:09,800
I feel less nervous now.

698
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:11,720
Thank you, Xiaomeng.

699
00:40:11,760 --> 00:40:12,560
It's fine.

700
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:14,400
Director.

701
00:40:15,520 --> 00:40:16,480
This is Zhou Xiaomeng.

702
00:40:16,840 --> 00:40:18,480
She used to be a host for a TV show.

703
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:20,880
Hello, Director.

704
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:22,120
My friend told me that

705
00:40:22,360 --> 00:40:24,240
your theater is recruiting.

706
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:26,080
I am here for an audition today.

707
00:40:27,640 --> 00:40:28,640
This is my resume.

708
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:31,200
Okay.

709
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:32,960
Let me finish the rehearsal
of this scene first.

710
00:40:33,160 --> 00:40:34,160
We will talk later.

711
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,200
Sure.

712
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:38,160
Action.

713
00:40:39,040 --> 00:40:41,720
Peter, we are talking about
how to go back.

714
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:43,480
I have prepared an elf

715
00:40:43,520 --> 00:40:44,520
to escort you back.

716
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:45,840
What I mean is,

717
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:47,680
you should come back with us.

718
00:40:47,920 --> 00:40:48,840
And then, what?

719
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:51,880
They'll send me to school and work.

720
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:54,720
Soon, I will become another person.

721
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:56,440
I don't want that.

722
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:58,080
I want to be a child forever

723
00:40:58,480 --> 00:41:00,200
to be happy forever.

724
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:02,080
You can't think like that.

725
00:41:02,240 --> 00:41:03,840
Grow up, Peter.

726
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:04,720
Good.

727
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:07,600
Very good. Keep up the good work.

728
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:10,120
Okay. Prepare for the next scene.

729
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:13,680
Let's go.

730
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:15,840
Director.

731
00:41:18,520 --> 00:41:19,800
I've read your resume,

732
00:41:20,320 --> 00:41:21,520
and I know who you are.

733
00:41:22,360 --> 00:41:24,800
I can explain about that incident.

734
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:27,680
It is actually not
what everyone thinks it is.

735
00:41:27,840 --> 00:41:28,960
Zhou Xiaomeng,

736
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,200
the host of children's program,

737
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:33,560
Fairy Tale Street.

738
00:41:33,800 --> 00:41:36,280
You have also published
some audio children books, right?

739
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:39,600
I thought you looked familiar.

740
00:41:39,840 --> 00:41:40,840
I didn't expect

741
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:42,600
you would come here for an audition.

742
00:41:43,160 --> 00:41:44,000
Thank you, Director.

743
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:47,120
But those are all things of the past.

744
00:41:48,280 --> 00:41:49,640
You were doing well as a host.

745
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:50,560
Why did you quit?

746
00:41:51,160 --> 00:41:53,600
I don't know if you have heard
about what happened to me.

747
00:41:54,360 --> 00:41:55,480
Now, I am

748
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:57,720
no longer fit for hosting
children's program.

749
00:41:58,320 --> 00:42:00,040
Is that about the photos on the Internet?

750
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:06,360
That was nothing.

751
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:09,680
It's natural for young people
to be ruthless and make mistakes.

752
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:10,840
It's nothing to be ashamed of.

753
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:12,320
I think what's shameful is

754
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:13,920
the person who took your photos

755
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:15,360
and put them on the Internet.

756
00:42:16,080 --> 00:42:16,880
What do you think?

757
00:42:17,080 --> 00:42:18,760
When can you start joining our rehearsal?

758
00:42:19,160 --> 00:42:20,040
I...

759
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:25,440
You mean I am hired?

760
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:28,560
Strictly speaking, you are on probation.

761
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:31,000
As you know,

762
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:34,880
theaters are having a hard time nowadays.

763
00:42:34,920 --> 00:42:35,720
The pressure is huge.

764
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:37,840
We produce children's plays

765
00:42:37,960 --> 00:42:39,840
which have even less audience
and hence more pressure.

766
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,400
So the wage

767
00:42:42,480 --> 00:42:45,320
can't be compared with what you got
as a TV host.

768
00:42:45,920 --> 00:42:47,400
I understand. It's all right.

769
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:48,680
Wage is not a problem.

770
00:42:48,880 --> 00:42:49,840
It's a deal then.

771
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:52,600
Our staff will contact you
for the remaining details.

772
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:54,440
At the beginning,

773
00:42:54,600 --> 00:42:57,880
you will help
with the on-site coordination,

774
00:42:58,320 --> 00:43:00,160
getting familiarized with our scripts

775
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:01,800
and taking notes.

776
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:03,880
Meanwhile,
let's get to know each other better.
